                <header class="article_header">
                    <h1>Currents Redesign</h1>
                    <h2>The Kauffman Foundation</h2>
                </header>
                <p>When The Kauffman Foundation decided to implement a new publishing strategy for their website, they needed a new digital format that could solve some unique challenges it would pose for their content authors. Their vision demanded the consolidation of many seemingly disparate content types (everything from press-releases to long-form editorial pieces) along with a need to display this content in a visually compelling yet cohesive manner. Our answer was to reach for a very specific UX / Design pattern that we knew would be up to the challenge: The Card Pattern.</p>

                <p>With a vast array of varied layout elements  and aesthetics, the unassuming Card Pattern would allow for <em>just enough</em> structured data to help content authors publish quickly, but also provide a strong foundation for unique content-first grid layouts. With an improved authoring experience, choices could be allowed for the fine-tuning of importance, weight, and visual hierarchy allowing the construction of an impactful “Featured Story Card” area <em>and</em> a browsable, dynamically-driven gallery of topic-based cards.</p>
            </section>
        </div>
