        <p class="gallery-caption">A sampling of the wide array of "Story Cards" made for the Currents redesign.</p>
        <section class="article_content article_content--bottom">
            <p>Each card was made up of shared meta-data: accompanying media (images, videos, patterns, etc.), short- and long-titles, descriptions, calls-to-action, and date-driven flags (such as “new”, “featured content”, etc.) so that no matter the original source, each card could be created within the CMS by simply choosing the appropriate card format (video, image, quote, etc.), a size based on importance and choosing a recently published story. From there a content author could tweak as needed; whether cropping a thumbnail for optimal placement, or word-smithing the perfect lead.</p>
        </section>
